threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, MIPS, MIPS32 version 1 (SYSV), too many section (65535)

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a sophisticated IoT botnet, likely a variant of Gafgyt/Qbot or Mirai, packed with UPX. It contains comprehensive malicious functionality including network scanning for weak credentials, DDoS attack vectors (XMAS, UDP, and Layer 7 HTTP floods), and persistence mechanisms via crontab, inittab, and rc.local manipulation. The sample actively cleans environment traces by setting HISTFILE to /dev/null and attempts to disable competing services (httpd, telnetd, sshd) to secure its hold on the infected device. It features a hardcoded credential list for brute-forcing and utilizes wget/curl/tftp to fetch and execute secondary shell scripts (1sh, 2sh, 3sh, tsh). Backdoor capabilities are evident through a 'cback' shell identified as 'bakunawa'.
